\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104qrs1665702859881.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qrs1665702859881.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/qrs1665702859881.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"qrs1665702859881\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Set breakpoints on ProcScript instructions, triggers, errors, or\n      conditions.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53300e1_d53301e1_d53302e1\">To set or remove a single breakpoint for a ProcScript instruction, you can:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53303e1_d53304e1_d53305e1\">Select it in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Module</span>\n                  pane of the debugger, right-click and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle\n                     Breakpoint</span>, click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle breakpoint</span> icon\n                     (<img alt=\"Toggle breakpoint icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__image_lsb_rmm_zwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/toggle1.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>), or choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Debug</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle Breakpoint</span></span>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53306e1_d53307e1_d53308e1\">Select it in the\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Browser</span> window, right-click and choose <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle\n                     Breakpoint</span>, or click the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Toggle breakpoint</span>\n                  icon  (<img alt=\"Toggle breaks point icon\" class=\"image\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__image_rtx_xmm_zwb\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/toggle1.gif?_LANG=enus\"/>).</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53309e1_d53310e1_d53311e1\">To add, edit, or remove multiple breakpoints multiple breakpoints at specific locations in ProcScript modules:\n <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53312e1_d53313e1_d53314e1\">Choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Debug</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Edit Breakpoints</span></span> and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Add</span>. <p class=\"p\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__p_d175190e1_d175191e1_d175192e1\">A line is added to the\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Location</span> list with initial values for\n                        <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span> and <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Module</span> names,\n                     and for the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Details</span> fields.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53315e1_d53316e1_d53317e1\">Enter the values for the\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Details</span> fields, then click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>.\n                  Refer to:<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"eka1665703524971.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eka1665703524971.html\" title=\"Add, remove, or edit multiple breakpoints at specific locations in your ProcScript modules.\">Managing breakpoints</a></li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53324e1_d53325e1_d53326e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yhe1665702860098.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yhe1665702860098.html\" title=\"Name of the ProcScript module.\">ProcScript Module for breakpoints</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53327e1_d53328e1_d53329e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fil1665702860168.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fil1665702860168.html\" title=\"ProcScript module line number where the breakpoint is located.\">ProcScript Line for breakpoints</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53330e1_d53331e1_d53332e1\">Optionally, enter a conditional expression in\n                  the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Breakpoint conditions</span> field. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53333e1_d53334e1_d53335e1\">To remove breakpoints, select the breakpoint\n                  in the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Location</span> list and click\n                     <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Remove</span>.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53336e1_d53337e1_d53338e1\">To set a breakpoint on specific triggers, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">View &gt;Settings</span></span> and click <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Triggers</span>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53339e1_d53340e1_d53341e1\">To set a breakpoint on the occurrence of specific\n            ProcScript errors, use the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Errors</span> tab of the\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Settings</span> form. See <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bxa1677053571070.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bxa1677053571070.html\">Working with Error and Exception related breakpoints</a> for\n            details.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">To set a breakpoint on the occurrence of exceptions, use the\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Errors</span> tab of the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Settings</span> form. See\n               <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bxa1677053571070.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bxa1677053571070.html\">Working with Error and Exception related breakpoints</a> for details.</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"qrs1665702859881__li_d53342e1_d53343e1_d53344e1\">To clear breakpoints, except for breaks on triggers\n            and ProcScript errors, choose <span class=\"ph menucascade\"><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Debug</span><abbr title=\"and then\"> &gt; </abbr><span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Clear All Breakpoints</span></span>. </li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ayx1665702860536.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Breakpoints</a><p>A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615496\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Working with breakpoints Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Set breakpoints on ProcScript instructions, triggers, errors, or conditions. To set or remove a single breakpoint for a ProcScript instruction, you can: Select it in the Module pane of the debugger, right-click and choose Toggle Breakpoint , click the Toggle breakpoint icon ( ), or choose Debug > Toggle Breakpoint . Select it in the Browser window, right-click and choose Toggle Breakpoint , or click the Toggle breakpoint icon ( ). To add, edit, or remove multiple breakpoints multiple breakpoints at specific locations in ProcScript modules: Choose Debug > Edit Breakpoints and click Add . A line is added to the Location list with initial values for Structure and Module names, and for the Details fields. Enter the values for the Details fields, then click OK . Refer to: Managing breakpoints ProcScript Module for breakpoints ProcScript Line for breakpoints Optionally, enter a conditional expression in the Breakpoint conditions field. To remove breakpoints, select the breakpoint in the Location list and click Remove . To set a breakpoint on specific triggers, choose View >Settings and click Triggers . To set a breakpoint on the occurrence of specific ProcScript errors, use the Errors tab of the Settings form. See Working with Error and Exception related breakpoints for details. To set a breakpoint on the occurrence of exceptions, use the Errors tab of the Settings form. See Working with Error and Exception related breakpoints for details. To clear breakpoints, except for breaks on triggers and ProcScript errors, choose Debug > Clear All Breakpoints . Related Links Breakpoints A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}